        <section class="top-section">
            <div class="flex-container-center-column">
                <img src="public/image/minecraft_tower.png" alt="Image of a tower" class="tower-image">
                <h1>Our rules</h1>
                <p class="paragraph-under-category-title">Before you can play we have a few rules you need to follow!
                </p>
            </div>


            <h3 id="1-general-rules" class="general-rules">1. General Rules</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Respect Others</strong> – Be friendly and respectful to all players. Do not insult, bully,
                    threaten, or harass others.</li>
                <li><strong>No Cheating</strong> – The use of hacks, X-ray, fly mods, or any form of cheating is
                    strictly prohibited. Exploiting bugs or glitches for unfair advantages is not allowed.</li>
                <li><strong>No Griefing or Stealing</strong> – Do not destroy or steal other players&#39; property,
                    including buildings, chests, items, farms, and animals, unless explicitly permitted.</li>
                <li><strong>No Inappropriate Content</strong> – Offensive content (sexual, racist, political, hate
                    speech, etc.) is not allowed in chat, builds, item names, or anywhere else.</li>
                <li><strong>Follow Admin Instructions</strong> – The decisions of administrators are final. If you
                    disagree, you may appeal through the proper channels. Do not insult or harass admins.</li>
                <li><strong>No Command Abuse</strong> – Do not abuse teleport (TP), home, or any other commands to
                    harass players, evade fights, or disrupt game balance.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">2. Building &amp; Land Claiming</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Respect Building Space</strong> – Do not build too close to others without permission. Keep
                    a reasonable distance to avoid interfering with others.</li>
                <li><strong>Large Constructions (e.g., Auto Farms, Mob Farms)</strong> – Must be built far from player
                    gathering areas to prevent lag or disruption.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Lighting</strong> – Place torches or other lighting around your builds to prevent
                    excessive mob spawns.</li>
                <li><strong>No Environmental Destruction</strong> – Avoid unnecessary damage to the landscape, such as
                    excessive lava/water placement, random digging, or deforestation.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">3. Resources &amp; Economy</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Shared Resources</strong> – Public farms and community chests are available, but always
                    replant and restock what you take.</li>
                <li><strong>Private Resources</strong> – Do not take items from personal chests, mines, or farms without
                    permission.</li>
                <li><strong>Fair Trading</strong> – Players may trade freely, but scamming, misleading trades, or
                    exploiting new players is prohibited.</li>
                <li><strong>No Resource Hoarding</strong> – Do not excessively monopolize biomes, mob spawners, or large
                    amounts of materials to maintain fair play.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">4. PvP Rules</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>PvP Only in Designated Areas</strong> – Combat is allowed only in specific PvP zones or with
                    mutual agreement. Unwanted PvP is prohibited.</li>
                <li><strong>No Killing Pets/Animals</strong> – Do not harm other players&#39; tamed pets or farm
                    animals, even in PvP.</li>
                <li><strong>Return Items After PvP</strong> – If a player dies in PvP, return their gear and items
                    unless they agree to forfeit them.</li>
                <li><strong>No TP-Killing</strong> – Do not use teleport commands to ambush or trap other players.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">5. Chat &amp; Communication</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Keep Chat Civil</strong> – No excessive swearing, spamming, or use of all caps. Do not
                    insult or provoke others.</li>
                <li><strong>No Advertising</strong> – Do not promote other servers or engage in real-money trading.</li>
                <li><strong>No Spreading Misinformation or Causing Drama</strong> – Avoid unnecessary conflicts and
                    disputes.</li>
                <li><strong>Use Appropriate Language</strong> – If the server has an official language, use it in public
                    chats to ensure inclusivity.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">6. Server Administration</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Obey Staff Instructions</strong> – Admins and moderators have the authority to enforce rules
                    and apply penalties.</li>
                <li><strong>Report Issues to Admins</strong> – Use Discord, private messages, or official reporting
                    methods to notify staff of any problems.</li>
                <li><strong>No Impersonating Staff</strong> – Do not use names similar to admin names or fake official
                    announcements.</li>
            </ol>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">7. Rule Violations &amp; Punishments</h3>
            <ul class="dotless-ul">
                <li>
                    <p><strong>First Offense</strong>: Warning or minor punishment (e.g., temporary mute).</p>
                    <p><strong>Repeated Offenses</strong>: Temporary ban or in-game penalties.</p>
                    <p><strong>Severe Violations</strong>: Permanent ban, possibly reported to the wider Minecraft community ban
                        lists.</p>
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h3 class="rule-section-title">8. Appeals &amp; Conflict Resolution</h3>
            <ul class="dotless-ul">
                <p>If you disagree with a punishment, you may appeal via the official Discord, email, or in-game feedback
                    system.</p>
                <p>Provide evidence (screenshots, videos, etc.) when submitting an appeal. Staff will review it within 24-48
                    hours.</p>
                <p>Resolve conflicts peacefully – Avoid personal revenge or escalating disputes.</p>
            </ul>
            <p class="last-text">✅ By playing on this server, you agree to follow these rules. Failure to comply may result in penalties
                and/or bans. ✅</p>

        </section>
        
